Uses of Package
perfcenter.baseclass

  • Packages that use perfcenter.baseclass 
    Package Description
    perfcenter.baseclass
    This package contains classes that define basic components of a distributed system.
    perfcenter.parser
    This package contains the classes used for parsing and storing the input file.
    perfcenter.simulator
    This package contains the improved classes over almost all classes of perfcenter.baseclass package.
    perfcenter.simulator.queue
    This package contains the classes that implement the Queue's simulation-time objects and book-keepings.
    perfcenter.simulator.queue.SchedulingStratergy
    This package contains the classes used for parsing and storing the input file.
    perfcenter.simulator.request
    This package contains the various Request classes that are used during the simulation to capture the flow of information.
  • Classes in perfcenter.baseclass used by perfcenter.baseclass 
    Class and Description
    Device
    This class defines devices that would be deployed on Host.
    DeviceCategory 
    DistributedSystem
    This is the complete representation of the input file.
    Distribution
    This represents a distribution.
    Lan
    Defines LAN.
    LanLink
    Used for defining connection parameters(mtu,prop,trans,headersize) between two lans
    Machine
    This represents the machine definition in the input file.
    Metric
    Holds value, confidence interval and confidence level of any performance or power metric.
    MigrationPolicyInfo 
    PhysicalDevice
    This class defines devices that would be deployed on Host.
    PhysicalMachine 
    Queue
    Queue class is the primitive queue which resides in all the components of distributed system.
    QueuingResource
    This class abstracts the queuing resources like Device, LanLink and SoftServer.
    Scenario
    This class holds a Scenario, as defined in the input file.
    ServiceTime
    Defines service times.
    SoftResource
    Defines soft resource.
    SoftServer
    Defines server .
    Task
    Defines the Task and operations done on task
    TaskNode
    This is used to make tree for a scenario
    Variable
    Stores the variable that is defined in the input file
    VirtualDevice
    This class defines virtual devices that would be deployed on Host.
    VirtualMachine
    This represents the virtual machine definition in the input file.
